image.altText: An ambulance in Melbourne's CBD.

props.synopsis: Victoria's paramedics union is blaming Ambulance Victoria management for any breaches of COVID restrictions when 40 staff attended a secret 2021 gathering to honour a colleague who had died.

title.children: Ambulance union defends paramedics for attending secret COVID-19 funeral gathering

image.altText: A map showing an emergency warning near Benloch, Victoria.

props.synopsis: Firefighters have controlled a blaze close to Benloch, where nearby residents were earlier warned to take shelter.

title.children: Firefighters gain upper hand against bushfire in Central Victoria

image.altText: Video still of an argument at an election forum

props.synopsis: Kooyong MP Monique Ryan has condemned gatecrashers who interrupted an election forum on Wednesday night, which saw one audience member throw a punch.

title.children: Kooyong forum descends into chaos after 'right-wing bullies' gatecrash

image.altText: Lines of blue and white police tape cross a busy city street where a police car is parked and officers stand.

props.synopsis: A 30-year-old man died from multiple stab wounds after a fight involving up to six people who allegedly chased him along Chapel Street during the early hours of Sunday morning.

title.children: A man has been charged with murder over Easter Chapel St stabbing

image.altText: Kyneton Football and Netball Club coach speaking to players.

props.synopsis: The AFL is set to review the circumstances around Kyneton Football Netball Club’s women’s side breaking away from the club, as more women's teams fold across the state.

title.children: Women's footy sides folding amid claims of a lack of support and understanding

image.altText: Woman wearing high vis vest passes box of produce to woman wearing red puffer jacket over the counter

props.synopsis: Green waste bins are supposed to reduce the amount of organic matter going to landfill, and in Geelong, it's also feeding residents.

title.children: What happens to the waste in our green bins? In Geelong, it's feeding the community

image.altText: The sign outside Casey Hospital with the hospital in the distance.

props.synopsis: Police have charged a man with a string of offences following an incident on Wednesday morning in which a woman accompanying her husband to hospital was allegedly struck by her own car.

title.children: Man, 25, charged after hit and run outside Melbourne hospital

image.altText: An older woman waits to cross a tree-lined street in a country town.

props.synopsis: London plane trees are a feature of many Australian towns and cities, but some say it's time they were removed amid mounting reports of infrastructure damage and pedestrian injuries.

title.children: Debate over whether to remove 'magnificent' street trees in Victoria

image.altText: A man in military type uniform and slouch hat on a horse

props.synopsis: A six-week journey on horseback through more than 30 rural towns has brought the story of the Australian Light Horse to life for students across country Australia.

title.children: History arrives on horseback for 14 students at rural school

image.altText: A blonde girl and her father stand side by side holding small Styrofoam packs with a deflated weather balloon attached.

props.synopsis: Pete Furphy was surprised to discover remnants of scientific research equipment that had travelled more than 300 kilometres when he and his kids helped clean a secluded south-west Victorian beach.

title.children: Discarded weather balloons wash up on Victorian shores

image.altText: Noah Balta of Richmond warms up preapring to collect a bouncing ball

props.synopsis: Richmond's Noah Balta speaks for the first time since his sentencing for an assault charge, expressing his remorse and apologising to the victim.

title.children: 'Violence is never the answer': Balta speaks for first time since sentencing

image.altText: A police car parked at the front of a Burberry store with a smashed window. Police tape along the front.

props.synopsis: Police arrested five men after raiding properties in Melbourne's south-east, seizing luxury items and stolen cars.

title.children: Men appear in court over luxury store ram raids in Melbourne

image.altText: A bishop in full robes.

props.synopsis: Mykola Bychok is the youngest cardinal in the Catholic Church and the only one with a link to Australia. He will join the conclave to elect a new pope.

title.children: Cardinal in Australia's swift rise to youngest man electing the new pope

image.altText: An aerial view of cars packed into a suburban development.

props.synopsis: McEwen is part new suburbs, part rural towns and part established suburbs, and it is a seat the Liberal Party will be working to take from Labor in the coming election.

title.children: Choked roads a major issue for voters in Melbourne's north

image.altText: Conor Nash watches Gryan Miers hobble off

props.synopsis: Hawthorn's Conor Nash is handed a four-game suspension by the AFL tribunal for a hit that left Geelong's Gryan Miers concussed.

title.children: 'Genuinely remorseful' Nash suspended for four weeks for Miers hit

image.altText: Police walking an arrested individual to a van

props.synopsis: Four people, including a patched member of the Rebels Outlaw Motorcycle Gang, are arrested as part of a police operation into an alleged drug trafficking syndicate in regional Victoria.

title.children: Rebels biker arrested in alleged million-dollar meth bust

image.altText: Woman in black blazer stands with her hands in front of her, green grass and bushes behind her

props.synopsis: The tertiary sector union says the opposition's election promise to restore the Australian home ownership dream by cutting international student enrolments is short-sighted and divisive.

title.children: Dutton's enrolment cap plan 'demonises' foreign students, union says

image.altText: Three photos of a woman holding and cooking with cottage cheese

props.synopsis: Supermarkets struggle to meet demand for cottage cheese as the product becomes the subject of viral videos.

title.children: Cottage cheese in short supply as TikTok trend drives popularity

image.altText: Caleb sitting on the beach digging a hole in the sand smiling.

props.synopsis: Locals are angry after a Victorian council deferred a vote on a motion to investigate ways to improve pedestrian safety on the road where six-year-old Caleb Wesley died last month.

title.children: Council delays vote on road safety motion despite Victorian boy's death

image.altText: A black and white photo of Australian cricketer Keith Stackpole.

props.synopsis: Former Australia Test opener Keith Stackpole dies, aged 84, after a dynamic career including seven centuries and a brilliant Ashes double ton.

title.children: Keith Stackpole remembered as 'a fantastic cricketer and a great bloke'

image.altText: Surfer Ramzi Boukhiam winces as he is carried up the beach.

props.synopsis: Moroccan surfer Ramzi Boukhiam suffers a "major injury" as he gets his foot stuck in the Bells Beach rocks and is hit in the knees by a wave while walking back to shore after his heat.

title.children: Surfer suffers bizarre injury as Bells wave takes him out at the knees

image.altText: A concept image of two workers in high-vis walking past a row of large batteries.

props.synopsis: A large battery project in South Australia sells for nearly $500 million as investment in renewable energy surges.

title.children: Millions invested in big batteries amid net zero transition

image.altText: A woman stands with a crowd of people behind her.

props.synopsis: From 1945 to 2022 Kooyong was Liberal heartland. Now it's a battleground as the Coalition try to reclaim it with allegations of dirty tricks from both sides being aired.

title.children: Liberal candidate accuses Monique Ryan of releasing 'dirt file' on her

image.altText: Abdifatah Ahmed sign

props.synopsis: About 200 people gathered in Melbourne's west to call for greater mental health supports after the police shooting death of Abdifatah Ahmed.

title.children: Hundreds gather to mourn man killed in Footscray police shooting

image.altText: Two detailed painted pieces of bark, black and white, sitting next to each other on a white wall.

props.synopsis: There are 23 artists who join forces in the TarraWarra Biennial where, tucked into the Victorian bush, art is giving voice to stories silenced by colonisation.

title.children: These artworks are about giving voice to stories too often silenced

image.altText: NSW Police at Bankstown address where woman kidnapping took place

props.synopsis: The woman's male partner's alleged involvement with organised crime is being investigated, said police, with two children known to the woman remaining in hospital under police guard.

title.children: Partner of woman found dead in burnt-out car had 'conflict' with crime group, police say

image.altText: Noah Balta, wearing a black gurnsey with yellow sash, celebrates next to the goal post

props.synopsis: Richmond footballer Noah Balta has been ordered to adhere to a curfew as part of his sentence for assaulting a man in a Mulwala car park last year.

title.children: Court curfew order rules Balta out of Anzac eve AFL clash

image.altText: Anthony Albanese and Monsignor Stuart Hall walk into a Catholic church

props.synopsis: Peter Dutton and Anthony Albanese both paid tribute to the late Pope Francis today, semi-suspending their campaigns before the third leaders' debate tonight.

title.children: A not-quite-suspended campaign sees leaders head to church

image.altText: A woman nurses a baby wombat wrapped in a blanket.

props.synopsis: The number of sick or injured wildlife is rising in Victoria, but the number of people able to help them is rapidly decreasing and carers say animals are being "left to die".

title.children: Wildlife carer spending $10k a year says cost is driving out volunteers

props.synopsis: John King captured footage of a 100-metre-tall fire tornado only 50 metres from his back door. Fire analysts say the phenomenon is becoming more common as the climate changes.

title.children: CFA volunteers were ready for fire season, but not for a 100m fire tornado

image.altText: Starters' blocks on a rain-soaked grass track at the Stawell Gift.

props.synopsis: Victorian athletics officials say they may have to review the benchmark time used for handicapping the Stawell Gift and other races, after the failure of Lachlan Kennedy and Gout Gout to reach the final.

title.children: Stawell Gift winner says 11m handicap 'totally fair' despite criticism

image.altText: Women in cricket gear train at Manuka oval

props.synopsis: After years of silence, the International Cricket Council has announced a task force and monetary fund to help support the exiled Afghan women's team, with hopes the money will match the sum given to the men's team.

title.children: 'Our voices finally heard': Plan for exiled Afghan women cricketers

image.altText: A young girl with her brown hair in a pony tail in a pink jumper holds her hands under her chin as she gazes at a keyboard.

props.synopsis: Parents and researchers hope the discovery of a genetic mutation could help find treatments for children living with previously undiagnosed neurodevelopmental disorders.

title.children: Discovery of genetic mutation leads to first diagnosis for dozens of kids

image.altText: Frank Carbone

props.synopsis: The vast majority of new arrivals in Australia end up in our capital cities. Experts and locals weigh in on how it's affecting our housing crisis.

title.children: The mayor of this Aussie suburb says it's 'full' as the migration debate heats up

image.altText: Two people in yellow high vis jackets stand at a bushy beach look out and look towards the sea.

props.synopsis: Authorities have ended a search for a Chinese national who was swept into the ocean near a popular Victorian tourist town on Good Friday.

title.children: Search called off for fisherman washed away at 'very dangerous' spot
